<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
        <title>404 - Page Not Found</title>
        <style>
            body {
                font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
                background-color: #f3f3f3;
                color: #333;
                margin: 0;
                padding: 0;
            }
            .container {
                max-width: 600px;
                margin: 100px auto;
                text-align: center;
                padding: 20px;
                background-color: #fff;
                border-radius: 8px;
                box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            }
            h1 {
                font-size: 36px;
                margin-bottom: 20px;
                color: #e74c3c;
            }
            p {
                font-size: 18px;
                margin-bottom: 30px;
            }
            a {
                color: #3498db;
                text-decoration: none;
            }
            a:hover {
                text-decoration: underline;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="container">
            <h1>404 - Page Not Found</h1>
            <p>Oops! It seems like you've reached a page that doesn't exist.</p>
            <p>
                Don't worry, you can go back to
                <a href="https://chdr.cs.ucf.edu/elle/home">ELLE's home page</a>
                or contact support for assistance.
            </p>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
